<br>
For myself, I don't really care too much as long as I at least get a roll on something I will use, (and on something no-one will use).<br>
<br>
But, of all the groups I've been in, I don't recall anyone joining a group and asking about the loot rules. I know I don't do this, and it would seem vaguely greedy to even ask, though I admit it would be the sensible thing, and would sort out some conflicts before they occur. There seems to be some basic assumptions going around about how loot will be handled, people don't feel the need to ask.<br>
<br>
The assumption is usually that it should be NBG, and in an ideal world, I'd prefer NBG, but when a 20k item drops, are you really going to trust the group member who you've never met before that he's going to use it? And how far do you take &quot;need&quot; - does that mean &quot;I'll use it all the time&quot;, or &quot;I'll use it situationally&quot;?<br>
<br>
So, anyway, how many of you ask about loot rules in a pickup group when you start it, or join it? Or do you typically assume what they're going to be?<br>
<br>
Just a few points to ponder, anyway.<br>
