<br>
I don't see it as greedy to ask what the loot method is when joining a group.  I always prefer the NBG method, but some people try to take advantage of it.  NBG does NOT mean &quot;my class can equip this item, yours can't&quot;  If it is an upgrade, then you NEED it.  If it's a weapon that will just be a toy, you do NOT NEED it.  &quot;Can use&quot; and &quot;Will use&quot; are different concepts and loot should be on a &quot;Will Use&quot; basis is NBG is called.<br>
<br>
On a side note, Clerics should get the majority of the cash loot, but not 100% of it IMO. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://users.adelphia.net/~sbetts21/images/NewSig3.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=149890"><br>
