 Most of us seem to have no problem with NBG, and I haven't seen anyone claiming a greed roll even on stuff like patterns if it could be used by a class in group.  Last weekend in HoH a &quot;longblade of vitality&quot; dropped, went NBG to pally, another one dropped and was greed rolled.  No hassle, no sweat.  <br>
Should someone insist on a greed roll against a (in the eye of most group members) justified NBG claim, most groups will do the roll, but you can be sure that the greed roller will not find a group there again, people take notes, and there is only so many guilds you can have a bad rep with to be basically blacklisted.<br>
You have to decide beforehand whether whatever you might be getting is worth a mark against your reputation.<br>
