<br>
When a big item drops - lets say for instance an <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=1059" target="top">Obulus Death Shroud</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  It's worth a fair bit because of the effect, it's a focus effect I personally value higher than flowing thought.<br>
<br>
Firstly it is ALL/ALL.  Lets assume your group is NBG and after an argument the Paladin is told to shut his face and he's finally accepted that.  In our fictional scenario that does not meen there is not a Mage in the group who has way better but still rolls so that he can sell it.<br>
<br>
Unless you have an instant-Magello such arbitary looting cannot exist fairly, there'll always be someone willing to phreak the system - afterall it's a pickup group.<br>
<br>
I cannot tell you how many times i've felt dissapointed at loosing out on loot to somebody I felt didn't really have a claim to it.<br>
<br>
These days I only do NBG when grouped with friends, if i'm with strangers then I will greed roll.  I don't roll to sell items though, so I do actually pick and choose what I roll on with a particular friend or alt in mind.<br>
