<br>
<br>
Not true for all players.  While I can afford to buy some upgrades for my main character(62 chanter), I don't.   Getting an equipment upgrade through battle is part of the fun of the game for me and I wont ever spend any time gearing up in the bazaar.   My gear, crappy as some of it is, comes from quests, group drops, my tradeskills, and raiding. Earning my gear instills a certain amount of pride for me in my toon.  So for me, it is need, not want.  While I don't have much in the way of time to play alts, the only twinking I do of them comes from gear I get through my main.<br>
<br>
*note* I'm not saying that folks who equip thier toons in different manners are wrong, just that they may derive enjoyment from EQ in different ways.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hibashira>Hibashira</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#330000>(7/10/03 11:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=856.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pickup group loot rules</span><hr size=1> I guess I look at it differently.  When I equip myself, I do it from bazaar.  That way, I don't have to worry about anything that might drop and the possible dispute that might come from it.  So what if this 10 Int 100 Mana uber loot dropped, grats to whoever.  I don't have to have it and I don't want to spend a second stewing over not getting it.  If you want it, its yours.  If everyone rolls, sure I'll throw in my /ran 1 1000.  Grats to the winner.  Done.  Now go pull that next mob.<br>
